  "prompt": "Is it true that Socrates was considered as a prophet in Islam?",
  "response": "In Islam, Socrates is not explicitly regarded as a prophet. The Islamic tradition recognizes a number of prophets, primarily those mentioned in the Qur'an, such as Adam, Noah, Abraham, Moses, Jesus, and Muhammad, who is considered the final prophet.\n\nHowever, Socrates is often discussed in Islamic philosophical literature as an influential figure in Western philosophy. Some Islamic scholars have acknowledged the contributions of philosophers like Socrates and have considered their ethical and philosophical thoughts. While he is respected for his pursuit of wisdom and inquiry into moral virtue, he does not hold the status of a prophet in Islamic belief. \n\nThe categorization of individuals like Socrates in Islamic thought can vary, but he is not typically included among the prophets.",
